{"id":"aristarchus","term":"Aristarchus","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Best ruler, native of Thessalonica (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 20:4\">Acts 20:4</a>), a companion of Paul (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 19:29\">Acts 19:29</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 27:2\">27:2</a>). He was Paul’s “fellow-prisoner” at Rome (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Colossians 4:10\">Col. 4:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Philemon 1:1\">Philemon 1</a>:24).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Acts 20:4","Acts 19:29","Acts 27:2","Colossians 4:10","Philemon 1:1"]}